{"id":11862,"date":"2020-01-22T14:47:23","date_gmt":"2020-01-22T13:47:23","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/www.mannheimerswartling.se\/?p=11862"},"modified":"2021-03-10T08:45:32","modified_gmt":"2021-03-10T07:45:32","slug":"cementa-is-granted-a-permit-to-expand-the-slite-quarry","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.mannheimerswartling.se\/en\/assignment\/cementa-is-granted-a-permit-to-expand-the-slite-quarry\/","title":{"rendered":"Cementa is granted a permit to expand the Slite quarry"},"content":{"rendered":"<p>The Land and Environment Court in Nacka has granted Cementa AB a permit to expand its quarry in Slite, Gotland. The permit allows for another 20 years of limestone mining. Limestone is the main component in cement and the quarry supplies Cementa&#8217;s cement factory in Slite. About two thirds of all concrete that is produced in Sweden is made from cement from this factory, and the permit secures a continued national supply of cement.<\/p>\n<p>Several authorities and organizations opposed the application, and the permit can be appealed to the Land and Environment Court of Appeal.<\/p>\n<p>Cementa is advised by Mannheimer Swartling in the permitting process.<\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>The Land and Environment Court in Nacka has granted Cementa AB a permit to expand its quarry in Slite, Gotland. The permit allows for another\u2026<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":8,"featured_media":0,"comment_status":"open","ping_status":"open","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":{"_acf_changed":false,"footnotes":""},"categories":[4313],"tags":[],"class_list":["post-11862","post","type-post","status-publish","format-standard","hentry","category-assignment","business-group-environment"],"acf":[],"lang":"en","translations":{"en":11862,"sv":11860},"pll_sync_post":[],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.mannheimerswartling.se\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/11862"}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.mannheimerswartl